    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Few Ways to Spend $60 Billion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Finley R Shapiro opposing $60 billion antimissile system</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's hard to believe that we need a system that would cost at least $60 billion to build, and an unknown amount to maintain and operate, to defend ourselves from a small, impoverished nation like North Korea (Week in Review, July 2).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It's hard to believe that we need a system that would cost at least $60 billion to build, and an unknown amount to maintain and operate, to defend ourselves from a small, impoverished nation like North Korea (Week in Review, July 2).</p>
        <p>We won't even be able to trust that the system will work. There must be a better, and less expensive, way.</p>
        <p>FINLEY R. SHAPIRO  Philadelphia, July 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
